{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_parsifal_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280608658/1957112801/1061.xml":{"full_text":"Hagerty Takes Aides\nOff the Hook on Illness\nBy MARTIN S. HAYDEN\nWhen Jim Hagerty got home, things got stuck bsck to\ngether again.\nThat*\u2019 how White House reporters are testifying in new\ntribute to the President's press secretary who. in a 12-hour\nperiod yesterday, kicked off a new \u201creassurance\" campaign on\nthe President's health, got White House doctors off the hook\non the words \u201cmild stroke\" and r\nstarted general repairs on dam\nage done by lack or candor\nthrough most of Tuesday as to\nwhat had really happened to\nMr. Eisenhower.\nWhen the President was\nstricken Monday Mr. Hagerty\nwas in Paris arranging for the\nDecember 15 NATO chiefs of\nstate meeting. Informed of the\nPresident's condition at a time\nwhen America thought it was\nnothing worse than \"a chill,\u201d\nhe was airborne within hours.\nAt 11:19 p.m. Tuesday h\u00bb-wa\u00bb\nback in a White House turned\ninto a public relations shambles\nby MaJ. Gen. Howard McC.\nSnyder, the President's phy\nsician. and Sherman Adams,\nthe White iHouse staff chief.\nThese ara the two men blamed\nby newsmen for the junking.\nIn Mr. pagerty's absence, of\nthe Hagtrty-tested policy of\ntelling in its most intimate\ndetail the whole truth about j\nEisenhower illnesses:\nSticks to Story\nSix hoars prior to Mr. Hag- 1\nerty\u2019i return hia assistant,:\nmotherly Anne Wheaton, had\nadmitted to the press that.\nwhile she was being made to!\nstick to the \u201cchill\u201d tale. Dr. i\nSnyder had known for 27 hours I\nthat the President had suffered;\na\u00ae occlusion, or stoppage, in\ntfte cerebral artery on the left'\n'ido of his head.\nSThe press secretary came\nbick to a conundrum that saw\n(Jen. Snyder (and Mrs. Wheat\nacting unddr his and Mr.\nams\u2019 orders) denying that?\ns constituted a \"mild stroke,\u201d j\n\u25a0a though its effects were\nl\u00dfce those which most people\noall a stroke. It remained for\nIfr. Hagarty tdexplain in terms\naeiyone could fnderstand why]\nt|ie President\u2019s doctors would!\nnot apply the sfrokC label to his\nffllment.\nThe Hagerty putting-together\nOs the pieces began at 8 a.m.\ntsie next day. First was the\nfamiliar \"operation reassur\n~z 1 '\"7\nt\nMHUI\nv j gp^^Jg BBSP\n\u25a0F v\nwc a- jy\nSnuggle Irifo our\nblissfully warm\nf\nLACE FRILLED\nCOTTON <bhK\nI CHALLIS r^\\SW\nlow price duo to a\nspectacular apocial purchaaat V\nChoice of full length (ahown) or N. y\nwalta length atyle. Both in white with blue,\nroae or lilae bowknota.\nMAIL AND PHONE ORDERS FILLED PROMPTLY\nIX. 3-6070\nlenda 1331 *T\u201c tl. H.W. 7 Coneara Shop. Center\nDowntown: Shop Monday, Friday,\nShop Friday, 9:30 to 9*o 9:30 to 9:30\nance,\u201d his heart attack and\nileitis-proved process of get\nting across the Idea that a sick\nPresident is brimming with re\ncovered health.\nThe President, he announced.\n,was up, had showered and\nshaved himself, had worked\nthrough a breakfast of creamed\nchipped beef, and had received\njhim and other visitors. A re\nporter asked about the Presi\ndent's stroke-induced speech\nimpairment.\nContinuing Tronble\n\"Oh yes,\u201d Hagerty recalled\ncasually, \u201che still has some\nI trouble with big words.\u201d\n(Asked if the President\nfussed about it, Mr. Hagerty\nsaid \"no he was laughing\nthis morning.\u201d He added\nthat \u201cwheh he would make a\nlittle slip, he would laugh and\nimmediately correct it.\u201d)\nWas the President capable\nof carrying on his official\nduties?\nMr. Hagerty had that issue]\ndisposed of by noon; on his!\ndesk were a dozen appointment\ncommissions, letters and other]\nofficial documents \u201cjust signed\u201d!\nby the President in'an obviously\nfirm hand. A half hour later;\ncame a casual announcement]\nthat Mr. Eisenhower was now]\ndressed in slacks and in a studio\nacross from hfc bedroom work\ning on a painting. He'd also;\njust conferred for t some min\nutes with Mr. Adams and Vice!\nPresident Nixon on NATO 1\nproblems, budget plans and\nother technical matters.\nAt a 1 p.m. session the secre\ntary deftly lifted Dr. Snyder\noff the \u201cno stroke\u201d hook.\nBacks Associates\n\u201cAdvisedly,\u201d Mr. Hagerty\nsaid, \u201cthe doctors decided\nagainst use of th4 word\nstroke' which is not a medical\nterm. It is chiefly associated:\nin the public mind with a\nbrain hemorrhage and result-\nant paralysis. Neither of thoae\ntwo things have happened to\nthe President. The doctors\nhafe been trying carefully to\navoid a connotation. Through\nuse of a lay term, that would\ngive the public a wrong report.\nThat is why we are not using\nthe word \u2019stroke.'\nOn one other item\u2014why tbe\ntrue story of the President\u2019s\nillness was concealed for 27\nhours\u2014Mr. Hagerty backed up\nhis associates, much as one\nmember of a family would\nstick by the others.\n\u201cI wasn\u2019t here.\u201d he said. \u201cI\u2019d\nrefer you to Mrs. Wheaton\u2019s\nexplanation last night.\"\nThe Wheaton story (dictated j\nby Dr. Snyder): The doctors\nwanted to be \u201csure\u201d of their\ndiagnosis before alarming the\nI public with it.\n(Mr. Hagerty also said that\nin any illness es the President\nit is \u201clawfully important\u201d to\nconfirm an ydiagnosis before\nit is announced to the world.\n\u2022As to whether he would\nhave handled news on the\nPresident\u2019s ailment any dif\nferently Tuesday if he had\n\\mmm\\\nI IN ALEXANDRIA\nrrr'.m. j,,,.,,,, I\nCENTRAL MOTOR CO. I,\n1201 Oronoco St. OV. 3-1500\nALEXANDRIA\u2019S ONLY MERCURY DEALER \u25a0l\nIn the Heart if Alexandria\u20144 Blacks From King St. h\nmm cin -sT- WWM\nWhile you carve ihe turkey today we slice prices\nlo the bona for unprecedented \u201cmid-season\u201d Thanksgiving\nBROADLOOM WWM\nSAVINGS\nmiss the extra beauty, extra warmth and friendliness your PDI A A A OUT A A A\nhouse can have this Holiday Seaton for just pennies a week* ||ilr lO Vi VA lIV lO 0\nTri-Tone